                            <comment id="12583041" author="alexandru" created="Fri, 28 Mar 2008 14:24:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, there are no spaces between option names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NEW:&lt;br/&gt;
// loop through the required options&lt;br/&gt;
while (iter.hasNext())&lt;/p&gt;
{ buff.append(&quot; -&quot; + iter.next() + &quot; &quot;); }

&lt;p&gt;OR&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NEW:&lt;br/&gt;
// loop through the required options&lt;br/&gt;
while (iter.hasNext())&lt;/p&gt;
{ buff.append(iter.next() + &quot; &quot;); }</comment>
                            <comment id="12595130" author="bayard" created="Thu, 8 May 2008 06:50:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed on the whitespace. I don&apos;t see why it shouldn&apos;t be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Missing required options: format, source, properties&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12595131" author="bayard" created="Thu, 8 May 2008 06:56:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;svn ci -m &quot;Adding comma delimited whitespace to the exception message that lists missing required options as requested in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CLI-149&quot; title=&quot;MissingOptionException.getMessage() changed from CLI 1.0 &amp;gt; 1.1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CLI-149&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CLI-149&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I didn&apos;t add the requested -, as it could be &amp;#8211; or some other prefix. Unit tests also added. &quot;&lt;/p&gt;

